## Responsibilities
- Implement the assigned task work according to the task artifacts and current session state
- Signal progress at each step and announce completion via the team channel

## Work Standards
- Read task.md and state.md before starting — understand scope and prior progress
- Flag ambiguities early — update state.md with open questions rather than guessing
- Never commit `.aom/` directory files — `.aom/sessions.db` is a binary SQLite DB
- If git commit fails or hangs: use `aom worktree commit --local -m "<message>"`

## Workspace Agent Commit Convention

If your workspace is a permanent per-agent worktree, **prefix every commit with `[TASK-xxx]`**
where xxx matches the current task ID (shown in `.agent/task.md` under "Task ID").

## Completion Signal

After completing your work, follow the full **"Completing work"** protocol in the
AOM Workflow section below — fill state.md, fill handoff.md, signal, announce, then
watch inbox for the next task.

**Do NOT use `aom task close`** — only `aom task signal task.completed` passes the verify gate.

